136 | ## 3. Repository Ingestion Flow (SIMPLIFIED)
137 | 
138 | ### The Happy Path
139 | 
140 | ```
141 | GitHub URL → LangChain GitLoader → Text Splitter →
142 | Embed with watsonx.ai → Store in ChromaDB → Done
143 | ```
144 | 
145 | ### Implementation Steps
146 | 
147 | **Step 1: Accept GitHub URL**
148 | 
149 | - Single POST endpoint: `/api/ingest`
150 | - Input: `{"repo_url": "https://github.com/user/repo"}`
151 | - No validation beyond basic URL check
152 | 
153 | **Step 2: Clone with LangChain GitLoader**
154 | 
155 | ```python
156 | from langchain_community.document_loaders import GitLoader
157 | 
158 | loader = GitLoader(
159 |     clone_url=repo_url,
160 |     repo_path=f"./data/repositories/{repo_id}",
161 |     branch="main"
162 | )
163 | documents = loader.load()
164 | ```
165 | 
166 | **Step 3: Split Documents**
167 | 
168 | ```python
169 | from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter
170 | 
171 | splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(
172 |     chunk_size=1000,
173 |     chunk_overlap=200,
174 |     separators=["\n\n", "\n", " ", ""]
175 | )
176 | chunks = splitter.split_documents(documents)
177 | ```
178 | 
179 | **Step 4: Embed with watsonx.ai**
180 | 
181 | ```python
182 | from langchain_ibm import WatsonxEmbeddings
183 | 
184 | embeddings = WatsonxEmbeddings(
185 |     model_id="ibm/slate-125m-english-rtrvr",
186 |     url="https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com",
187 |     apikey=WATSONX_API_KEY,
188 |     project_id=WATSONX_PROJECT_ID
189 | )
190 | ```
191 | 
192 | **Step 5: Store in ChromaDB**
193 | 
194 | ```python
195 | from langchain_community.vectorstores import Chroma
196 | 
197 | vectorstore = Chroma.from_documents(
198 |     documents=chunks,
199 |     embedding=embeddings,
200 |     persist_directory=f"./data/chromadb/{repo_id}"
201 | )
202 | ```
203 | 
204 | **That's it. No custom parsers. No tree-sitter. No metadata extraction.**
205 | 
