208 | ## 4. Query Processing Flow (SIMPLIFIED)
209 | 
210 | ### The Happy Path
211 | 
212 | ```
213 | User Question → Embed Question →
214 | ChromaDB Similarity Search → Build Prompt →
215 | watsonx.ai Granite → Stream Response
216 | ```
217 | 
218 | ### Implementation Steps
219 | 
220 | **Step 1: Accept Query**
221 | 
222 | - Single POST endpoint: `/api/query`
223 | - Input: `{"repo_id": "uuid", "question": "How does auth work?"}`
224 | 
225 | **Step 2: Retrieve Context**
226 | 
227 | ```python
228 | # Load existing vectorstore
229 | vectorstore = Chroma(
230 |     persist_directory=f"./data/chromadb/{repo_id}",
231 |     embedding_function=embeddings
232 | )
233 | 
234 | # Similarity search
235 | docs = vectorstore.similarity_search(question, k=5)
236 | context = "\n\n".join([doc.page_content for doc in docs])
237 | ```
238 | 
239 | **Step 3: Build Simple Prompt**
240 | 
241 | ```python
242 | prompt = f"""You are a code assistant. Answer the question based on this code:
243 | 
244 | CODE CONTEXT:
245 | {context}
246 | 
247 | QUESTION: {question}
248 | 
249 | ANSWER:"""
250 | ```
251 | 
252 | **Step 4: Call watsonx.ai Granite**
253 | 
254 | ```python
255 | from langchain_ibm import WatsonxLLM
256 | 
257 | llm = WatsonxLLM(
258 |     model_id="ibm/granite-3-8b-instruct",
259 |     url="https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com",
260 |     apikey=WATSONX_API_KEY,
261 |     project_id=WATSONX_PROJECT_ID,
262 |     params={
263 |         "max_new_tokens": 1000,
264 |         "temperature": 0.3,
265 |     }
266 | )
267 | 
268 | response = llm.invoke(prompt)
269 | ```
270 | 
271 | **Step 5: Return Response**
272 | 
273 | ```python
274 | return {"answer": response, "sources": [doc.metadata for doc in docs]}
275 | ```
276 | 
277 | **No streaming initially. No caching. No re-ranking. Just works.**
