<content># RepoLens Frontend

React/Next.js frontend for RepoLens - Chat with Your Codebase.

## Overview

This is the web interface for RepoLens, allowing users to:
- Submit GitHub repository URLs for ingestion
- Track ingestion progress in real-time
- Ask natural language questions about the codebase
- View AI-generated answers with source code references

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **HTTP Client:** Axios
- **AI Backend:** FastAPI + watsonx.ai Granite

## Project Structure

```
repolens-frontend/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx           # Main application page
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout with metadata
│   └── globals.css        # Global styles
├── components/
│   ├── RepoInput.tsx      # Repository URL input & status
│   ├── ChatBox.tsx        # Question input field
│   └── MessageList.tsx    # Chat message display
├── services/
│   └── api.ts             # Backend API service layer
├── types/
│   └── api.ts             # TypeScript type definitions
└── .env.local             # Environment variables
```

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ and npm
- Backend API running on `http://localhost:8000`

### Installation

1. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

2. Configure environment variables:
```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
# Edit .env.local if backend is not on localhost:8000
```

3. Run development server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

4. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser

## Usage

### 1. Ingest a Repository

- Enter a public GitHub repository URL (e.g., `https://github.com/user/repo`)
- Click "Ingest" button
- Wait for ingestion to complete (progress bar shows status)

### 2. Ask Questions

Once ingestion is complete:
- Type your question in the chat box
- Press Enter or click "Send"
- View the AI-generated answer with source file references

### Example Questions

- "What does this repository do?"
- "How does the authentication work?"
- "Explain the main components"
- "What dependencies does this project use?"
- "How is error handling implemented?"

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | Backend API base URL | `http://localhost:8000` |

## API Integration

The frontend communicates with the FastAPI backend through these endpoints:

- `POST /api/ingest` - Submit repository for ingestion
- `GET /api/ingest/{repo_id}/status` - Check ingestion progress
- `POST /api/query` - Ask questions about the repository
- `GET /api/health` - Health check

See `services/api.ts` for implementation details.

## Development

### Build for Production

```bash
npm run build
npm start
```

### Linting

```bash
npm run lint
```

## Features

✅ **Real-time Ingestion Tracking** - Progress bar shows ingestion status  
✅ **Chat Interface** - Clean, intuitive Q&A interface  
✅ **Source References** - Answers include file paths from the codebase  
✅ **Error Handling** - User-friendly error messages  
✅ **Responsive Design** - Works on desktop and mobile  
✅ **Loading States** - Visual feedback during API calls  

## Troubleshooting

### Backend Connection Issues

If you see connection errors:
1. Verify backend is running: `curl http://localhost:8000/api/health`
2. Check `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in `.env.local`
3. Ensure CORS is enabled in backend

### Ingestion Fails

- Verify the GitHub URL is public and accessible
- Check backend logs for detailed error messages
- Ensure watsonx.ai credentials are configured in backend

## Built With

- [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) - React framework
- [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) - Utility-first CSS
- [Axios](https://axios-http.com/) - HTTP client
- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/) - Type safety

## License

See LICENSE file in root directory.

